HEADWORD: Griddle
<hw>Grid"dle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>gredil</ets>, <ets>gredl</ets>, <ets>gridel</ets>, of Celtic
origin; cf. W. <ets>greidell</ets>, Ir. <ets>greideal</ets>,
<ets>greideil</ets>, griddle, gridiron, <ets>greadaim</ets> I burn,
scorch. Cf. <er>Gridiron</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>An iron plate or
pan used for cooking cakes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A sieve with a wire bottom, used by
miners.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Griddlecake</ent>⟦br⟧
